<TITLE> Germany bans far-right youth group </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BERLIN, Tue Mar 31,(bdnews24.com/Reuters) - German Interior Minister Wolfgang Schaeuble banned right-wing organization "Heimattreue Deutsche Jugend" on Tuesday, saying the group was spreading Nazi propaganda to young people. The organization, Patriotic German Youth in English, has several hundred members, the ministry said. It called it a cornerstone of the far-right movement with ties to the National Democratic Party (NPD). "With today's ban we're putting an end to the nauseating activities of the HDJ," Schaeuble said in a statement. "We're going to do everything possible to protect our children and our youths from these rat catchers." The ministry, which also said police had raided homes and offices of the HDJ in four states early on Tuesday, said children had been given lessons at camps portraying foreigners and Jews as a threat. Schaeuble has increased the pressure on far-right extremist groups over the last year amid calls to try to ban the far-right NPD after a first attempt failed in 2003. Last May, he banned two other far-right organizations that he said were "reservoirs of organized Holocaust deniers." Denying the Holocaust is illegal in Ger
